race.comment: DARKNCONFIDENTIAL (2) had been threatening to win a race and did so in great fashion last start. Holder sticks and there's every reason to think he can go on with it here. TALISAY (6) has mixed her form a little this time but on her best she is more than capable. She's drawn well and gets in with 54.5kg for Milnes. Hard to think she won't be in the finish. KOMACHI (1) broke through for a deserved win last start and can go on with it here. Barrier 1 and Pannell aboard are positives. Respect the winning form from over the border of SIR ROCKFORD (4), who is open to further improvement third-up. If you're looking for one at a price, the old boy MAGNETIC EDGE (3) might be able to run a cheeky race at a price with the 3kg claim.
